Text.Value: To begin the pre-operational test, press and hold the CLR/TEST button until a complete display appears, then release the button.
The following sequence of numbers are displayed:
• .000 µGy
• 66.6 cGy
• 1.11 µGy
• 777 cGy
• 22.2 µGy
• 88.8 Gy
• 333 µGy
• 999 Gy
• .444 cGy
• 5.55 cGy
• 9 (Blinking)

A flashing "4" with three dashes above it, followed in about 10 seconds by a blinking "9", indicates that the combination of the neutron and gamma pulse detectors is nearing 1,000 cGy of total dose accumulation. The AN/UDR-14 Radiacmeter is entirely functional, including all forms of dose measurement, and the flashing "4" is displayed to alert the user that the dosimeter assembly should be replaced in the near future by maintenance personnel.
